parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine can cause loss of control, accidents, and leave the driver stranded, especially in heavy traffic or hazardous weather conditions.

the vehicle stalls at high speeds
the vehicle stalls on the highway.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unusual noise and vibration from the engine can be a sign of a more serious underlying issue, potentially leading to engine failure, stalling, or loss of control.
symptoms: The engine makes a tapping sound
the engine makes a metal-on-metal vibration noise
especially during acceleration and deceleration
the engine noise is accompanied by vibration.

the engine needs to be replaced

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air fuel sensor can cause the engine to run rich or lean, leading to poor performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially causing the engine to stall or fail.
symptoms: The air fuel sensor has possibly failed.

the transmission becomes stuck

causing injury or distraction.
